http://www.thehindu.com/news/cities/chennai/One-killed-as-speeding-car-rams-parked-autorickshaws/article14533214.ece

In a shocking road accident, one person was killed when a Porsche car rammed some autorickshaws parked on Cathedral Road in Chennai in the early hours of Monday. Some of the drivers were sleeping inside the vehicles.One person has been detained in connection with the incident, police said. It is suspected that the person was under the influence of alcohol.Sources said Arumugam died of head injury and Varadhan suffered a left frontal bone fracture.A total of nine persons were brought to the Government Royapettah Hospital at 2 a.m. Of these, seven were treated and discharged.(With inputs from Zubeda Hamid)